      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "METCALFE (2) just missed a place at the Sunshine Coast and then was just beaten over 1900m at Kilcoy. Well-seasoned for the step-up to a staying trip, and a senior hoop replaces the apprentice. LITTLE LUNCH (7) was in the market in Maiden company over 2170m at Ipswich, off a distant placing on the Gold Coast poly. Sits down in the weights and shapes as if the longer journey will suit. PREFER TO DANCE (3) found a place over 2180 at Ipswich in stronger and will be better for it. Has Lloyd aboard and can make a better fist of this trip since his try at it here in September. ALASKA DE LUNE (6) would be in the finish at best and is also a hope in a weak race. LINAS REEL (1) has a 2kg claim and the tongue tie on for the first time and has scope for improvement.",
